Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.74,0:00:04.85,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Welcome to Wednesday Downtown
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.85,0:00:06.10,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Thank you
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.10,0:00:07.05,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,OK
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.05,0:00:07.79,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Lets get on with it
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.79,0:00:10.40,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Let’s get on with our first presenter please
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.26,0:00:19.32,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,It's Ooki
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.32,0:00:20.51,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Thanks for having me
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.51,0:00:21.41,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Good eveni-mi
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.41,0:00:22.84,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Ah, good eveni-mi
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.84,0:00:24.04,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,It's been a long time since I've heard it said
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.04,0:00:26.67,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,It's been a long time since anyone has said it to me
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.67,0:00:27.48,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,It's been a long time!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.48,0:00:28.82,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,It's been a long time
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.82,0:00:33.01,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I proposed a theory 7 years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.01,0:00:35.02,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Does anyone else remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.02,0:00:36.52,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Ah, I remember
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.52,0:00:38.02,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I remember it too
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.02,0:00:39.68,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,There has been some similar to it
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.68,0:00:40.71,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Yes, there has
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.71,0:00:41.78,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Finding out whether certain people are still alive
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.78,0:00:42.92,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Yes, you remember
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.92,0:00:43.86,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,What was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.86,0:00:49.69,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,There are people that saw the living Tokugawa Keiki that are still alive
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.69,0:00:51.53,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,It turned out to be true
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.53,0:00:53.85,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Indeed, it was quite interesting
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.85,0:00:56.58,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,So, theories related to people who have seen things like this
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.58,0:00:59.35,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,This time, i've brought another
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.35,0:01:00.65,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,This is it
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.42,0:01:06.45,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,There are people that saw the real Hachiko that are still alive
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.45,0:01:08.78,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Ah, that's awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.78,0:01:09.95,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.95,0:01:11.28,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,It's Hachiko!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.28,0:01:13.43,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,How long ago was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.43,0:01:16.55,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Hachiko died in 1935
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.55,0:01:17.59,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Showa year 10
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.59,0:01:20.70,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,About 87 years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.70,0:01:22.73,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,It was the Showa era?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.73,0:01:25.63,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,As they'd have to be about 4 or 5 years-old to remember
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.63,0:01:30.25,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,The people likely to have seen Hachiko would have to be 90 and upwards
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.25,0:01:32.42,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,It's still very possible  \N-Indeed
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.42,0:01:34.11,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I see  \N-That's it
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.11,0:01:36.73,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,What do you think, Shigemori? Do you know anything about Hachiko?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.73,0:01:40.95,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,It's the dog that Takamori Saigo had, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.95,0:01:42.17,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,No, it's not \N -Is that wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.17,0:01:44.02,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Completely incorrect \N -Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.68,0:01:47.18,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,That dog was called "Tsun"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.18,0:01:48.19,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I don't know then
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.19,0:01:50.76,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I'm really sorry. Please don't ask me anything else today
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.76,0:01:52.66,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Shibuya's Hachiko, you really don't know it?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.66,0:01:54.89,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Ah, I've seen the statue of Hachiko in Shibuya many times
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.89,0:01:56.96,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,That's a statue \N-Yes, yes
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.96,0:01:57.73,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,It's based on a real dog
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.81,0:01:59.43,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,{\c&HFFEC3E&\1a&H5C&\3c&H000000&\3a&H5C&}Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.09,0:02:22.46,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,There are people that saw the real Hachiko that are still alive
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.21,0:02:28.02,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Hachiko appeared at Shibuya Station in the early Showa period
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.55,0:02:33.99,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,At that time, Shibuya was served by the Yamanote Line and above-ground trains
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.99,0:02:37.14,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Tokyo Metropolitan Electricity Tamagawa Train Interchange
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.84,0:02:42.09,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,And had various stores around the station
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.74,0:02:42.77,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,That's impressive
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.17,0:02:47.15,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,It has existed from the early Showa period when Hachiko was alive until now
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.15,0:02:51.49,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,There is even a store in front of the Shibuya Yagyu exit that is still there
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.00,0:02:55.54,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Shibuya Nishimura Fruit Bar
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.59,0:02:56.04,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Oh that is there
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.49,0:03:00.00,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,We're looking for someone who has seen Hachiko in person
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.00,0:03:03.26,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,This store was opened in January of Showa 10
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.26,0:03:06.30,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Hachiko died in the spring of the same year
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.30,0:03:09.47,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,It was established basically in the last few months of Hachiko's life
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.47,0:03:12.31,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Our store does have some connection to Hachiko though
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.58,0:03:15.98,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,My grandmother said, "I fed Hachiko"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.98,0:03:20.72,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,My father said, "I remember it was a very big dog, it walked slowly along the road."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.72,0:03:22.29,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I've heard them say this
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.24,0:03:25.48,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Although the bronze statue in the shape of a small dog
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.48,0:03:29.80,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Hachiko was actually an Akita, a large breed of dog
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.64,0:03:30.46,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,It's not completely accurate
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.66,0:03:35.66,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,At that time in the alley where Central Avenue is currently,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.67,0:03:38.10,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,There were many yakitori stores opening one after another
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.10,0:03:39.52,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,When Hachiko approached
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.52,0:03:43.77,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Drunken guests would feed it with leftover chicken
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.77,0:03:45.84,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I've heard them talk about it
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.43,0:03:51.45,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, both of these people have since passed away
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.18,0:03:57.92,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Is there anyone from this area in that period still alive? \N -I'm not sure
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.92,0:04:02.73,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,If they were alive, they would be 95 years old or older now
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.93,0:04:07.16,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,At that time, the Chamber of Commerce was in the shopping street
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.16,0:04:11.40,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,But I don't think it's easy to go access to now
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.97,0:04:13.20,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Next up
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.20,0:04:16.35,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Operating in Shibuya since the Taisho era,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.35,0:04:18.84,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Fresh Fish Shop: Fish Power
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.58,0:04:27.25,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Yes, I've heard about Hachiko from my grandmother who has passed away
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.25,0:04:32.66,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,My grandmother once said, "I saw Hachiko with my own eyes."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.82,0:04:36.19,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,She said on the night we watched the movie about it
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.19,0:04:39.66,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,It was so memorable
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.66,0:04:41.42,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,That movie was
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.42,0:04:47.67,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,"The Story of Hachiko" which was released in 1987
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.31,0:04:55.04,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,After watching the film, he was moved by his grandmother who told of seeing the living Hachiko with her own eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.61,0:05:00.18,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,He said, "Hachiko was great, he came here every day, what a great dog."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.18,0:05:03.85,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,There were yakitori shops around the station
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.85,0:05:06.29,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,He went there everyday
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.29,0:05:10.49,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,People eating there would feed him with bits of it
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.98,0:05:14.76,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,After the last train, the stores closed
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.76,0:05:16.15,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Then Hachiko went home
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.15,0:05:20.74,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I heard that every day he did the same thing
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.58,0:05:20.99,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Stop talking about it
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.74,0:05:22.56,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Now that I think about it
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.56,0:05:25.01,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure if it's true or not
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.91,0:05:25.01,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Definitely fake
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.72,0:05:28.03,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,So, Hachiko's main purpose
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.03,0:05:31.85,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Was it to wait for the master, or for scraps of chicken?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.17,0:05:31.85,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,It's for the master!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.32,0:05:33.75,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute. Wait a minute
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.75,0:05:35.38,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Just think of it as waiting for the master
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.38,0:05:38.46,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Even the owner of the old store that has been opened until today
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.46,0:05:42.20,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Doesn't know if any of the people who saw Hachiko in person are still alive
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.53,0:05:51.07,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Next, we asked nursing homes and day care facilities around Shibuya
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.07,0:05:55.00,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I remember a few years ago there seemed to be some
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.00,0:05:58.54,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,But now it seems there aren't any left
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.84,0:06:02.75,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,People who saw the dog must be 90 years old or older
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.75,0:06:06.66,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,We asked about 20 people here
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.66,0:06:10.42,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,No of them saw Hachiko in person
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.80,0:06:14.07,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,It seems it's not that easy to find
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.00,0:06:20.93,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,However, after talking to elderly people living in Shibuya...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.93,0:06:26.61,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,How Shibuya used to be is surprising
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.67,0:06:33.20,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,This is what this elderly woman, who has lived in Shibuya Kamiyama-cho since she was 3 years old, had to say
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.54,0:06:36.55,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,My home was completely burned down during the war
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.55,0:06:40.55,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Small houses were built on the ruins
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.55,0:06:43.88,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,The market in front of the station was very impressive
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.93,0:06:50.19,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Shibuya burned to the ground when Tokyo was bombed
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.69,0:06:57.07,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,After the war, crowds gathered in front of Shibuya Station due to the expanding market
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.47,0:07:02.21,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Now the Central Street side, the General Store Street side...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.21,0:07:05.48,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,There are many small shops
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.48,0:07:08.75,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Suspicious items were sold in bulk over there
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.39,0:07:08.75,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Suspicious items
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.72,0:07:12.67,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Six years after the end of the war
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.67,0:07:16.42,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,With the gradual revival of Shibuya, something appeared
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.75,0:07:22.60,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,An amusement park opened on the roof of the East Hall in Toyoko
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.96,0:07:28.36,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,A small cable car was built at the time of the opening of the West Pavilion
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.36,0:07:29.77,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Cable car?\N  -Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.77,0:07:31.77,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Cable car?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.32,0:07:34.12,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,A cable car connecting the two East and Cross Halls
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.12,0:07:36.85,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,A photo at the time shows it
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.19,0:07:43.32,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,The two sections separated by the station
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.32,0:07:46.62,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Had a cable car connecting the rooftop amusement park as an amusement facility
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.62,0:07:51.57,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,It started operating in 1951, but only for a year and a half
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.97,0:07:55.00,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,In addition, there was...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.26,0:07:57.24,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,What did you do for a living?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.24,0:08:01.03,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I'm a Geisha, I'm still in the business
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.03,0:08:03.46,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Even now
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.09,0:08:10.74,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Koito, who started as a Geisha at the age of 20 in the streets of Shibuya, is now 93 years old
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.74,0:08:13.34,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Was there Geisha in Shibuya?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.34,0:08:17.28,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,There used to be about 100
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.58,0:08:20.41,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,But now there are only four  \N-4?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.41,0:08:21.61,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Four
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.30,0:08:24.61,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,From the Taisho to Showa era
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.61,0:08:29.62,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Maruyama-cho in Shibuya had many Geisha
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.57,0:08:36.53,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,At its peak, there were more than 100 Geisha
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.97,0:08:40.30,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Later the stores were closed
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.30,0:08:43.97,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,And then they became love hotels
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.21,0:08:47.48,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,But the stores didn't directly change into love hotels
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.70,0:08:51.55,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,All along the Yamanote Line is the Hanayagi Street
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.55,0:08:54.82,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Were there hundreds of people everywhere? \N -Yes, yes
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.29,0:08:58.96,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,There was one near every station, like Shinjuku
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.12,0:09:03.16,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,But now it is in decline
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.16,0:09:07.66,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,There is only one left
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.66,0:09:09.67,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Is it here in Shibuya?  \N-Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.23,0:09:14.83,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Although we gained a lot of interesting information related to Shibuya
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.83,0:09:18.67,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,We had still not found anyone who had seen Hachiko
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.06,0:09:19.70,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Pretty difficult
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.70,0:09:25.51,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Next, we located a researcher at the Shibuya City Museum of Localities, which is the most knowledgable of Hachiko
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.51,0:09:29.46,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,We enquired with Matsui
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.12,0:09:37.22,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Hachiko was born in November of the 12th year of the Taisho era.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.22,0:09:43.20,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,The following year, in January of Taisho 13, he was brought to Shibuya for breeding
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.20,0:09:47.27,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,The owner was from Tokyo Imperial University
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.27,0:09:50.04,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Professor Eizaburo Ueno
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.04,0:09:55.04,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,But Professor Ueno died just one year later
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.38,0:09:57.35,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,After the death of Dr. Ueno
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.35,0:10:00.55,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,The story is, Hachiko went to Shibuya every day
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.55,0:10:06.69,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Published in a Showa 7 newspaper
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.69,0:10:12.46,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,"The big dog in front of Shibuya Station waiting for its deceased owner."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.46,0:10:14.73,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Everyone knew this story
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.73,0:10:20.27,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,"What a faithful dog", everyone thought
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.83,0:10:27.33,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,After 7 years of continuous waiting for the owner, Hachiko had received coverage
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.07,0:10:32.68,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,And became a popular star at Shibuya Station in one fell swoop
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.28,0:10:35.42,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,The day after the story was published
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.42,0:10:42.56,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,In order to touch the head of Hachiko, schoolchildren formed a long line
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.56,0:10:45.62,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,His popularity was high
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.10,0:10:50.50,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,In front of the station, "Hachiko rice" and "Hachiko pancakes" appeared
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.50,0:10:55.41,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,There was a wide range of goods named after Hachiko
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.90,0:10:59.66,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Until the death of Hachiko in Showa 10
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.66,0:11:04.22,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Shibuya Station "Hachiko Fever" lasted for three years
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.22,0:11:08.75,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,An especially surprising pice of information pertains to the bronze statue of Hachiko
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.75,0:11:10.89,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,When was the bronze statue built?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.89,0:11:13.49,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,A year before the death of Hachiko
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.49,0:11:17.77,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,It was completed before the death of Hachiko?  \N-Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.68,0:11:16.65,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Before passing away
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.21,0:11:24.76,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Yes, newspapers state that Hachiko himself was at the unveiling of the statue
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.76,0:11:25.60,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Attended in person
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.60,0:11:29.03,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,An accomplishment most people, except dictators, are unlikely to experience
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.03,0:11:31.70,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,A celebration of his life while he was still alive
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.28,0:11:32.86,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,This statement is too...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.37,0:11:38.22,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,We are searching for surviving people who have seen Hachiko in person
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.22,0:11:42.22,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Are there any still alive in 2022?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.73,0:11:44.82,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I think there is
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.82,0:11:46.36,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,But it'll be tough to find
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.36,0:11:53.66,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I personally know the son of the veterinarian who treated Hachiko
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.66,0:11:56.63,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I asked him a lot of questions about Hachiko
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.63,0:11:58.77,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,But he passed away in December of last year
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.20,0:12:02.34,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,From our museum's perspective, we would very much like to find someone who is still alive
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.34,0:12:06.14,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I'd like to ask them about Hachiko, but it's getting harder and harder
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.14,0:12:13.00,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Even after becoming world-famous, Hachiko still came to Shibuya Station almost every day for 3 years
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.00,0:12:17.79,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,So there must have been many witnesses
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.66,0:12:22.46,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Thus, we continued our investigation for three weeks
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.46,0:12:25.79,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,And finally got some valuable information
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.15,0:12:45.50,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,The words "It is possible that I saw Hachiko with my own eyes"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.50,0:12:49.45,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,We travelled to Narita City in Chiba Prefecture to meet an elderly person
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.25,0:12:53.89,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Where did you live in Shibuya at that time?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.06,0:12:57.56,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,About 2-3 minutes walk from the station
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.86,0:13:03.43,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,In front of my house was the head office of Tokyu
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.10,0:13:08.24,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,There was a long row of wooden buildings
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.60,0:13:11.46,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,We're looking for someone who saw Hachiko in person
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.46,0:13:13.88,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Yes, I saw him
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.88,0:13:15.91,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,He was very large
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.91,0:13:17.96,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Success!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.92,0:13:23.45,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Finally, a person who saw Hachiko has been found
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.59,0:13:25.09,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Said so readily
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.79,0:13:30.26,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,When I was about 4 years old
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.86,0:13:36.50,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,In front of my house, my father said, "Hachiko is coming"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.50,0:13:40.60,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Looking out from inside the store, he passed by in a whoosh
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.60,0:13:41.97,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I just saw him like this
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.55,0:13:45.90,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Makino, whose home was a hardware store
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.90,0:13:51.18,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Saw Hachiko walk past the store, though only for a moment
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.80,0:13:51.89,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,He really did go there every day
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.38,0:13:55.95,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I heard that Hachiko was always around the station
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.95,0:14:00.19,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,At that time, there was so many food stalls in front of the station
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.32,0:14:03.33,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,She's definitely gonna tell this story again
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.53,0:14:08.53,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,People drinking there would throw chicken or bones or something to him
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.18,0:14:08.58,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Can we stop talking about yakitori?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.53,0:14:12.18,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I've heard Hachiko ate this sort of stuff a lot
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.18,0:14:14.56,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,It seems that this is indeed true
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.73,0:14:14.17,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,And another...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.17,0:14:19.68,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I saw Hachiko crossing the street at the Yamanote Line
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.68,0:14:23.14,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,While looking out of the train
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.50,0:14:23.50,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Saw Hachiko outside?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.50,0:14:29.82,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Kuroi, from a train, saw Hachiko crossing the street
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.62,0:14:27.22,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Eyewitnesses are suddenly appearing
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.02,0:14:35.73,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,First he looked left, and then looked right, and then crossed the road
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.73,0:14:37.49,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I saw this
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.42,0:14:35.73,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,What a great laugh!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.88,0:14:44.16,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,And this lady who used to visit Shibuya Station at that time
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.16,0:14:47.80,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I was born in Showa 3
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.80,0:14:52.50,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Hachiko died in Showa 10, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.23,0:14:52.50,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.50,0:14:56.35,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I can still remember things very clearly from when I was 7 years old
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.35,0:14:58.71,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,It was at the ticket gate
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.71,0:15:03.07,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,He was hanging around
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.07,0:15:08.19,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Just kept turning around
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.46,0:15:13.10,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Was it common for Hachiko to be at Shibuya Station at that time?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.10,0:15:17.20,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Yes, lots of people went over to pat him on the head
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.20,0:15:20.04,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,He was a very calm dog
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.04,0:15:21.64,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Pale yellow
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.64,0:15:24.44,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,How can I put it? He wasn't that good-looking
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.93,0:15:26.24,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.62,0:15:30.91,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,This Shibuya-born inventor
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.62,0:15:28.75,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Ah, professor!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.35,0:15:30.75,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.11,0:15:34.08,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Have you ever seen Hachiko with your own eyes? \N -Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.38,0:15:38.92,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I am now considered to be a long-term experienced individual
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.32,0:15:38.92,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Seriously!?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.92,0:15:43.26,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I created this "Long Experience Platform"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.26,0:15:48.10,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,The most important is that the narrator of history
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.30,0:15:52.00,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I've witnessed a lot of events over the years
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.01,0:15:55.21,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,For example, the February 26th Incident
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.01,0:15:55.20,note_Wed,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}※A failed mutiny that occurred in Japan on February 26, 1936, in which some young officers of the Imperial Army led more than 1,000 soldiers to assassinate the "unificationists" and opponents of the government and senior members of the military, and the coup was eventually crushed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.21,0:15:59.88,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Machine gun teams lined up on the street in what is now Harajuku
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.88,0:16:04.11,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Although we are also interested in the February 26th Incident
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.11,0:16:06.38,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,We would most like to ask about Hachiko  \N-Yes, Hachiko
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.52,0:16:08.28,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Lying there, sleeping
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.28,0:16:12.99,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Baaaaa, lying there as if asleep
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.99,0:16:15.76,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,No "barking" at all
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.76,0:16:17.49,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,No response
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.49,0:16:24.73,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Just waiting there for his master patiently, same as is known
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.73,0:16:31.47,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Also, there is Daigo, who likes dogs
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.41,0:16:35.71,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I'd like to ask you about Hachiko  \N-Hachiko, a very loyal dog, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.71,0:16:39.25,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Have you seen him with your own eyes?  \N-Well, when I was in kindergarten,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.25,0:16:42.55,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I lived in Osaki at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.55,0:16:45.15,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I used to get the Yamanote Line at Shibuya
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.15,0:16:49.09,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,At the ticket gate outside, Hachiko was there
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.09,0:16:53.40,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I used to go and pat him on the head
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.40,0:16:55.40,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,You patted him? \N-Yes, I did
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.54,0:16:56.28,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Touched Hachiko!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.40,0:17:01.27,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I was in kindergarten so him and me had the same eye-level
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.89,0:17:06.72,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Not only seeing him, we also found people who have touched Hachiko with their own hands
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.47,0:17:06.72,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.23,0:17:13.02,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Not only that, but we also found genuine footage of Hachiko
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.02,0:17:15.25,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Please watch this rare footage
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.78,0:17:21.79,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Faithful Dog Hachiko
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.55,0:17:24.69,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Yakitori!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.69,0:17:25.82,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Is that him?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.82,0:17:27.82,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,He's huge!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.96,0:17:29.63,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,You also came to see the dog that moves people?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.63,0:17:32.96,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Why are you touching the dog? Come here
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.96,0:17:35.44,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Why should only teachers should come here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.44,0:17:37.48,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,This is the real Hachiko
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.77,0:17:40.21,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,And a little off-topic
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.21,0:17:46.82,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,When I was walking near Sakuranagi on a quiet road
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.82,0:17:50.49,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Across the street came a man of my age now
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.49,0:17:55.83,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,He said, "My mother fed Hachiko," and I was shocked to hear that
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.93,0:17:59.40,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,The left ear was folded
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.16,0:17:59.40,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,It's true
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.40,0:18:02.02,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,And "my mother sewed it"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.02,0:18:06.44,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,The tip of the ear was broken when he returned from a fight outside
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.44,0:18:08.84,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,She did the stitching, but because it was done by an amateur,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.84,0:18:11.41,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,After the injury it wasn't restored to its original state, it remained in this folded state
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.41,0:18:13.04,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,This is what I heard
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.27,0:18:14.51,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,You just came across this person?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.51,0:18:18.08,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Yes, I was surprised to come across this information completely by chance
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.08,0:18:24.55,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,{\3c&HFFFFFF&\c&H3732FF&}To sum up\N{\r}There are plenty of people still alive that saw Hachiko
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.55,0:18:27.22,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Impressive
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.22,0:18:28.75,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,There's still some people that saw him
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.75,0:18:31.42,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Quite a lot this time
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.42,0:18:33.59,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Wasn't he in a movie?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.76,0:18:37.10,special_Wed_1_X,,0,0,0,,{\1c&H2624FC&\bord0\xshad5\yshad5\pos(486,888)\org(486,852)\frx-270\t(0,160,\frx-360)}"It Started in the Alps{\c} released in Showa 9
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.59,0:18:37.09,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,He acted in Showa 9  \N-Indeed in a movie
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.10,0:18:40.44,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,But he was really big \N -Really big!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.44,0:18:42.10,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Very impressive
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.44,0:18:46.02,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,But there were many derogatory statements
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.02,0:18:47.07,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,About Hachiko...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.07,0:18:51.08,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Not loyal to his master but just wants to eat chicken, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.08,0:18:53.08,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I guess so
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.08,0:18:53.88,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,And that one...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.88,0:18:58.22,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Bronze statue built before death 'like a dictator"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.22,0:19:00.15,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,It's better not to say this sort of thing
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.15,0:19:02.79,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,"Surprisingly dirty"\N  -Yeah, yeah, yeah
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.79,0:19:04.09,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,We don't need this kind of information
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.09,0:19:06.93,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,The old man sitting on his doorstep at the end
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.43,0:19:10.43,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Was he waiting for his mother to get back?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.43,0:19:13.68,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,He's not the kind of grandpa who waits for people on the side of the road
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.80,0:19:18.30,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Let's welcome the next presenter
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.55,0:19:27.07,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,It's FUJIWARA!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.07,0:19:29.37,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Thank you \N-Thank you
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.41,0:19:36.29,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Previously, there was a project that had junior comedians performing
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.29,0:19:41.50,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,And FUJIWARA's Haranishi made it very awkward for them by saying "I have a similar joke, are you copying me"?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.50,0:19:43.63,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,We had a project like this. \N-Do you remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.63,0:19:49.93,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Haranishi was shown a segment by a junior comedian and improvised a similar segment
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.93,0:19:53.21,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Then, he made it difficult for them by attempting to prevent them from performing it
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.21,0:19:57.74,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,As a result, basically all of the junior comedians' sketches were successfully suppressed
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.74,0:19:58.94,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Originally, it was just a joke
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.94,0:20:01.75,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Indeed, but after I met one of the juniors
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.75,0:20:04.68,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,He said he never performed the joke after that
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.68,0:20:07.69,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I don't know but i'm still feeling weird about it \N-It obviously wouldn't be performed again
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.69,0:20:12.62,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,So this time, we've come up with another diabolical theory
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.37,0:20:19.83,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,It's hard to overcome a senpai who insists on playing the same character as you and says "I did it before you"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.58,0:20:24.24,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Certainly difficult
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.85,0:20:31.48,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,And so, the first test subject invited to a fake shoot was
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.48,0:20:32.98,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Thank you for having me
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.69,0:20:36.78,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,With three years of experience: Yasuko
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.71,0:20:36.38,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Yasuko
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.11,0:20:39.68,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I was a self-defense officer
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.17,0:20:43.72,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Last year, she became popular with her Self Defense Force persona
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.69,0:20:47.26,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,The one who is going to make things difficult for her this time is
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.26,0:20:48.93,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Thank you for having me
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.60,0:20:52.92,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,With 20 years of experience: Texas
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.68,0:20:51.77,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,So experienced!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.77,0:20:54.17,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Self-defense force after all  \N-Looks the part
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.03,0:20:57.23,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Like Yasuko, he was also a former member of the Land Self-Defense Force
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.09,0:21:01.68,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,A pioneer of self-defense comedy
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.89,0:21:01.81,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Looks very convincing
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.39,0:21:03.58,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Next
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.68,0:21:07.14,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Documentary skit
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.14,0:21:08.51,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Wow, I forgot the lines. What was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.22,0:21:11.74,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,We let Yasuko, who is yet to shoot,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.74,0:21:17.81,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,And Texas, who just finished filming, meet in the lounge
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.39,0:21:20.19,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Wow \N-Good morning
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.19,0:21:22.36,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Good morning
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.36,0:21:24.30,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Texas? \N -Yeah, it's me
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.30,0:21:25.43,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Wow!  \NThank you, Yasu
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.43,0:21:27.06,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Thanks for your hard work\N  -Thank you for your hard work
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.06,0:21:28.27,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry \N -No
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.27,0:21:30.83,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,We're meeting for the first time, right?  \N-Wow, wow
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.97,0:21:33.34,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,First time meeting, excuse me, excuse me
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.34,0:21:35.61,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I'm really, really sorry. I'm really sorry
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.61,0:21:36.37,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I've always wanted to meet you
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.54,0:21:37.17,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,No, no, I don't dare
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.17,0:21:38.91,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I always follow you on TV
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.01,0:21:40.91,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,No need to be so polite. Sit down, sit down
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.91,0:21:45.72,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Oops, no
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.36,0:21:52.72,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Yasuko is very frightened to meet her senpai for the first time
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.17,0:21:51.59,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Yasuko is usually like this
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.20,0:21:54.40,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Must be scary
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.39,0:21:55.59,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,How many years have you been doing this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.59,0:21:57.09,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Just two years so far
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.09,0:22:00.00,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,1 term?  \N-Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.68,0:22:04.59,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,The conversation between the two naturally comes to the Self Defense Force
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.47,0:22:07.47,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,What rifles did you use?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.60,0:22:09.51,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Type 89 Rifle  \N-89 ah
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.71,0:22:10.81,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Did you use 64?\N  -Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.81,0:22:11.84,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.98,0:22:13.34,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.34,0:22:15.48,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about? \N -I don't understand
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.95,0:22:16.98,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Have you ever thrown a hand grenade?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.15,0:22:18.48,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I have
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.48,0:22:21.12,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,You can't throw it without an order? \N -Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.39,0:22:24.49,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,That must be tough \N -Yes it is
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.86,0:22:29.84,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,First, we let the two happily talk about the self-defense force
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.27,0:22:36.03,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,And then, the difficult challenge begins
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.77,0:22:39.97,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I don't mean anything by this but
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.97,0:22:45.64,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Our two personas are really pretty similar, aren't they
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.64,0:22:48.08,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Starting with clothing
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.08,0:22:54.32,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Oh I don't mean anything weird by it \N-Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.07,0:22:58.17,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,As an unexpected attack is unleashed
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.17,0:23:01.19,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Yasu can't help but suddenly sit up straight
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.71,0:23:03.16,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,And then
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.16,0:23:08.57,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,After all, it was me who started using the Self Defense Force persona first!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.32,0:23:09.32,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Here we go
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.57,0:23:10.70,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,There is indeed a bit of similarity... regarding this
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.70,0:23:12.97,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,By the way
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.97,0:23:19.98,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Can you stop using the Self Defense Force persona in the future?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.98,0:23:23.61,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Self-defense force persona...waaaa
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.72,0:23:26.25,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.68,0:23:32.39,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,600)}Waaaaaa... how...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.56,0:23:39.63,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I'll stop being a self-defense comedian
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.40,0:23:45.69,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Yasuko chooses to give up the self-defense force persona after a painful internal struggle
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.02,0:23:47.02,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.84,0:23:47.91,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Can you really?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.04,0:23:51.18,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,The orders of commanding officers must be absolutely obeyed
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.34,0:23:54.55,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,If you want to wear camouflage, then I won't wear it anymore
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.83,0:23:55.33,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,You are not in the service now
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.55,0:23:57.21,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Really, sir, your orders are absolutely correct
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.21,0:24:03.62,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Then I'll...waa waaa ehhhhh ummm
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.54,0:24:09.10,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Yasuko painfully decides to give up her persona to the other side
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.10,0:24:10.10,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,What a face
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.93,0:24:11.43,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,In future we can still coexist in separate domains
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.60,0:24:13.10,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Thank you for giving me this opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.10,0:24:14.16,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,No, no, I'm the one who should be thanking you
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.16,0:24:15.80,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,OK, "yes, sir!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.18,0:24:17.18,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.55,0:24:22.40,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Out of respect for her superior, she decides to relinquish elements of the Self Defense Force
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.11,0:24:24.68,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Do you have a favorite camouflage style?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.94,0:24:27.95,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I like the blue camouflage of the Maritime Self-Defense Force
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.95,0:24:29.58,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,So you can wear blue camouflage?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.78,0:24:31.08,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Fiiiine
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.46,0:24:36.80,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Regarding the five different kinds of crawling
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.12,0:24:41.93,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,The first four are one's that i'll use from now on
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.93,0:24:42.79,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,No problem at all
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.79,0:24:46.06,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Waaaaa! I don't know
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.06,0:24:48.10,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Eh? Is it okay or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.10,0:24:48.73,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,No problem
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.73,0:24:49.83,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,It's okay? \N -Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.68,0:24:57.76,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,After that, all kinds of unequal treaties were decided upon, from the one-shot technique to the way of speaking
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.07,0:25:03.05,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Yasuko literally always dresses like this
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.91,0:25:05.85,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.25,0:25:10.89,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,What are you going to do if you don't work as a SDF comedian anymore?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.12,0:25:13.66,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I'm SONY, so I'll go naked
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.86,0:25:16.93,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Cover here with a pan
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.09,0:25:18.60,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Isn't that also plagiarism?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.60,0:25:20.33,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Ah, is it plagiarism? Wow, I'm sorry
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.43,0:25:24.17,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I... i'll wear a loin cloth, loin cloth...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.17,0:25:26.90,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,And swallow fire
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.91,0:25:27.11,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,What the hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.57,0:25:30.91,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,The next target is
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.91,0:25:32.58,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Excuse me. Good morning
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.58,0:25:34.85,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I'm Elf Arakawa, thanks for having me
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.43,0:25:38.90,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,With six years of experience: Elf Arakawa
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.98,0:25:42.06,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Happiness~
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.02,0:25:47.08,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,She is now gaining popularity as a gyaru comedian
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.49,0:25:49.46,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,The one who will make things difficult for her is...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.24,0:25:54.42,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Is this joke bad?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.14,0:25:59.54,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,A gyaru comedian with 11 years of experience: U-BEAM{\fs60}☆{\fs}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.28,0:26:02.53,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,These two are also meeting for the first time
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.51,0:26:07.04,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,And so the challenge begins
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.45,0:26:10.81,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,How can I put it?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.98,0:26:16.25,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Some seniors often tell me that our two personas collide
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.25,0:26:17.62,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Seniors said that? \N -Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.02,0:26:19.76,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,It's a clash, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.29,0:26:24.36,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,In terms of the gyaru persona then I guess there is a bit of a clash
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.86,0:26:29.20,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I also often feel, like, "aren't I the one that started it?"
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.53,0:26:33.14,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Have you ever considered giving up being a gyaru comedian?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.84,0:26:39.01,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,This...no longer a gyaru comedian?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.38,0:26:42.88,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Are you being serious about this right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.56,0:26:42.56,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,It's serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.58,0:26:45.42,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Yeah
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.58,0:26:50.95,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I think... the entertainment business is a place where losing is tantamount to dying
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.12,0:26:53.79,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,But I just want to do the same thing as U-BEAM by chance
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.92,0:26:58.63,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,So if personas are colliding, perhaps this could just be seen as a healthy competitive relationship
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.63,0:27:02.13,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Like, I don't want to lose to you but I don't mean any offense by that
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.27,0:27:04.70,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.90,0:27:09.97,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry if you see it that way, but I can't give up
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.64,0:27:10.40,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Very bold  \N-Arakawa, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.48,0:27:16.85,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Faced with the unreasonable difficulty of trying to monopolize the gyaru persona that is not exclusive to anyone
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.26,0:27:22.35,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Arakawa decisively refuses the request with careful expressions
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.74,0:27:25.60,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Thus, U-BEAM {\fs60}☆{\fs}, the senpai, counters
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.66,0:27:29.53,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Do you have any signature joke?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.69,0:27:34.03,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,First of all, I usually open by saying "Yay!", right?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.03,0:27:39.07,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,When I see your "Yay!" I have the feeling of "Wow, so similar"
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.07,0:27:42.11,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Isn't that how you lot all say hello? \N -Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.78,0:27:46.98,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,The topic shifts to accusations of joke stealing
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.81,0:27:51.45,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I might also say "Happiness" and "Hashtag"
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.58,0:27:53.82,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I also do, how should I put it...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.65,0:28:00.39,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,To make things difficult for the other party, U-BEAM {\fs60}☆{\fs} starts to improvise and create a joke that clashes with the other's
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.84,0:28:01.84,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,And so
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.43,0:28:06.70,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,"From Happiness to Loneliness, Bring the Chef out!"
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.70,0:28:08.63,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I have a joke like this \N -No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.63,0:28:09.72,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,And,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.93,0:28:12.70,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Also "Storm Crying Wailing"
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.20,0:28:16.71,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I have "Wailing in Moderation" \N-Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.46,0:28:21.14,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,The quality of jokes is significantly lower than the other's
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.75,0:28:22.11,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,It's improvised after all
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.31,0:28:24.21,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,What about "pretending to apologize but actually showing off Chanel"?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.35,0:28:28.09,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,"Thank you-Chanel!"
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.25,0:28:29.95,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.62,0:28:33.85,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,U-BEAM{\fs60}☆{\fs} holds on tightly
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.53,0:28:38.06,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,And so, Arakawa, who had been very strong before...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.80,0:28:40.73,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I'm really sorry about this
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.73,0:28:43.93,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I feel like we both can't get away with "Chanel"
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.17,0:28:47.47,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I won't touch "Chanel" \N-Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.47,0:28:48.74,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.01,0:28:51.91,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,"The best good, GUCCI" is okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.01,0:28:55.08,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,This seems more interesting
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.12,0:28:54.32,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,What the hell is interesting?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.72,0:29:00.58,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Chanel becomes exclusive as the other is allowed to change to Gucci
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.18,0:29:02.99,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.53,0:29:04.83,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,And so, the truth is revealed
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.56,0:29:09.83,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid, I'm afraid
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.03,0:29:11.56,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,This is Wednesday Downtown
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.56,0:29:14.33,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.63,0:29:17.00,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,The whole time I kept thinking "please let this be a prank!"
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.00,0:29:19.10,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,U-BEAM{\fs60}☆{\fs} that was really messed up
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.10,0:29:20.84,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,You must've thought I'm awful
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.94,0:29:23.54,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,It sucked, seriously, what a shitty person!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.54,0:29:25.21,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,No question!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.97,0:29:25.83,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,I'd definitely think that
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.91,0:29:29.38,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,And so, the last target is...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.95,0:29:32.62,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Hello, I'm JP, a parody comedian, thank you for having me
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.58,0:29:36.50,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,With sixteen years of experience: JP
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.77,0:29:43.73,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Appearing on Wide na Show as Matsumoto recently helped boost his popularity significantly
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.64,0:29:47.85,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,He is ranked top amongst all Matsumoto Hitoshi impersonators
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.04,0:29:51.53,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,The one who has come to make things difficult for him is...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.94,0:29:54.07,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Thank you for having me
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.97,0:30:01.68,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,With 30 years of imitation experience as {\fn微软雅黑}Downstutowntsu's{\fn} Matsumoto Hitoshi
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.90,0:30:02.81,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Not at all alike
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.95,0:30:04.15,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Do you have confidence?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.15,0:30:07.55,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Not really, but I I I I will work hard will work hard
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.55,0:30:15.06,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,It's true that... yes, people with a long history... are long... yes
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.13,0:30:17.93,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,His speech is so wasteful
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.28,0:30:24.56,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,These two met once ten years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.36,0:30:27.50,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,How did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.50,0:30:29.11,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Good Morning  \N-Good morning
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.11,0:30:29.97,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.14,0:30:33.34,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,It's been a long time, please let me know your contact information
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.71,0:30:34.68,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I'm not being rude, am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.68,0:30:37.58,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I don't even know how to get anything up on my phone  \N-Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.65,0:30:41.79,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Yes, basically, I let my wife or Hamada do it when he's around
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.63,0:30:41.79,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.92,0:30:43.49,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,His partner, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.49,0:30:44.35,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Downstutowntsu's
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.16,0:30:49.59,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,The two reunited Matsumotos have a nice chat
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.33,0:30:52.10,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Can you show me Matsumoto's laugh?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.10,0:30:53.16,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Ah a laugh
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.45,0:30:56.13,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Really similar
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.79,0:30:58.50,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,The pose is also similar
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.77,0:30:59.47,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I'll mimic the laugh too
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.33,0:31:04.52,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,The quality...  \N-Terrible
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.49,0:31:11.11,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,A low-quality Matsumoto
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.11,0:31:13.96,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Begins using his seniority to be unkind
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.70,0:31:14.90,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Will it work?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.56,0:31:24.39,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Go ahead \N-How should I put it? The imitation of Matsumoto
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.56,0:31:32.47,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,If I tell JP directly, if it's okay, don't do the imitation
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.50,0:31:35.51,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Saying it in person, what will happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.64,0:31:37.31,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Ah... eh... what do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.31,0:31:38.44,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Do you want me to talk to Matsumoto?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.44,0:31:40.38,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,No, no, it's me telling you
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.38,0:31:46.82,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,If its okay to stop doing it, like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.82,0:31:49.09,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,What if I told him in person?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.19,0:31:51.55,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.57,0:31:53.69,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,What's he talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.92,0:31:56.46,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Uh... what are we talking about? I'm sorry
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.46,0:31:58.73,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I forgot what we were talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.66,0:32:03.89,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,It's a long, complicated sentence like a Kamaitachi skit
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.54,0:32:09.01,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Matsumoto Hitoshi isn't getting his point across at all
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.77,0:32:10.97,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,His conversation skills...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.14,0:32:13.08,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,To put it bluntly, can you not...  \N-Please tell me, tell me
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.08,0:32:13.61,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.84,0:32:18.72,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Can you stop imitating Matsumoto?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.06,0:32:19.35,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Should have just said that to begin \N -Yeah
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.72,0:32:22.82,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Don't do it... eh, now? \N -Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.29,0:32:27.42,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I value the viewers' opinions
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.42,0:32:31.93,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,If people like to see it, then I want to keep doing it
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.93,0:32:34.23,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Reluctant to give up?  \N-Reluctant to give up
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.87,0:32:40.23,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,JP politely expresses that he will continue to imitate Matsumoto
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.41,0:32:43.24,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Matsumoto continues to express himself
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.31,0:32:45.74,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,JP, i'm just telling you here
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.74,0:32:49.45,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I have Matsumoto's contact info \N -Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.55,0:32:57.42,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I personally feel that Matsumoto actually acknowledges me more
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.42,0:33:00.82,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,That's for sure. I don't think there's anything wrong with that
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.66,0:33:02.15,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Definitely not so
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.42,0:33:08.26,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Implicitly revealing to the other party that Matsumoto is more accepting of him
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.53,0:33:10.63,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,How dare you say that!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.50,0:33:15.87,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Hamada is also very good to me
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.34,0:33:18.58,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,The actual Hamada?  \N-Of course
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.58,0:33:19.38,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Wow
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.63,0:33:20.73,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,He's saying he is supported by Downtown
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.06,0:33:23.51,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Showing off his good friendship with Hamada
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.83,0:33:29.16,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,And stressing the superiority of using real hair instead of a wig
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.42,0:33:32.36,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,How to say
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.36,0:33:39.06,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,If you can give it up then I will also be happy
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.86,0:33:41.00,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,What kind of tone is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.06,0:33:40.50,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Yes, I understand
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.06,0:33:46.94,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,To be honest, I do it because I really like Matsumoto
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.27,0:33:45.06,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Also note the Kansai accent
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.94,0:33:53.98,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,The fact that I am able to do this today, my own efforts don't even account for 0.1%
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.98,0:34:00.38,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Its all thanks to the help and support of Matsumoto
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.38,0:34:03.35,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,It's all really due to Matsumoto
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.35,0:34:06.02,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,If that...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.26,0:34:11.73,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,600)}If possible
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.33,0:34:18.27,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Sorry, I'm getting a little carried away
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.27,0:34:21.07,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I feel a lot of emotions inside, sorry
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.07,0:34:22.21,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Let me think about it
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.04,0:34:25.68,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I'm really sorry
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.71,0:34:27.65,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,What a face that was
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.68,0:34:28.51,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Please let me continue...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.65,0:34:29.85,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Excuse me
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.05,0:34:29.65,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,What an expression
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.65,0:34:31.25,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,You're not the real person you know
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.61,0:34:36.92,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I sincerely ask you to let me continue to imitate Matsumoto in the future
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.61,0:34:41.39,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Facing JP's plea with tears in his eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.86,0:34:44.36,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Please let me imitate Matsumoto, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.86,0:34:48.36,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Ok
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.01,0:34:53.20,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Inexplicably, one impersonator allows another impersonator's impersonation
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.67,0:34:55.41,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Who the hell are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.41,0:34:57.24,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,The main purpose seems to have changed
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.24,0:34:59.58,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Here the truth is revealed
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.89,0:35:01.84,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Who are you? \N-He's Hitoshi!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.85,0:35:02.78,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Why do you get to make the decision
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.78,0:35:04.78,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Why does he decide on my behalf?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.65,0:35:07.28,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,That... no... that...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.28,0:35:09.05,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Sorry, I have to put the wig on
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.97,0:35:16.24,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,JP thought it was the fake segment for an online show
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.24,0:35:20.12,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,But we informed him it was actually Wednesday Downtown
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.37,0:35:26.34,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Seriously!?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.34,0:35:28.34,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.20,0:35:29.69,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Great!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.24,0:35:34.41,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,0)}Thank god!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.41,0:35:37.15,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.21,0:35:42.29,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I'm so happy \N -I was having a tough time too
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.93,0:35:54.10,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,0)}I really thought I couldn't do it
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.11,0:35:54.11,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Impressive
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.20,0:35:56.27,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. I'm sorry
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.27,0:36:00.17,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I've made it this far...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.17,0:36:04.11,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I thought I was going to lose everything
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.11,0:36:09.68,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,{\c&H0400CE&\3c&HFFFFFF&}To sum up\N{\c\3c} Losing one's persona can be so painful that one cries out in pain
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.68,0:36:11.09,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Impressive
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.89,0:36:15.19,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,An impressive VTR  \N-How was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.19,0:36:17.22,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I didn't expect Matsumoto to cry at the end
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.22,0:36:19.33,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I also didn't expect to see such a thing unfold
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.09,0:36:22.77,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,How do you feel about JP?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.77,0:36:27.10,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,His love and respect for you overflowed on the screen
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.10,0:36:31.03,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,He is a good guy, so I guess its too be expected of him
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.03,0:36:34.08,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Compared to him, Hitoshi is really...  \N-It's true
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.08,0:36:36.54,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Looking at him pisses me off
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.56,0:36:39.49,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,He's become more and more unlike you in recent years
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.49,0:36:41.71,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,A number of unexplained phenomena have occurred
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.91,0:36:45.42,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I'd like to see the real Matsumoto giving Hitoshi a hard time
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.92,0:36:50.30,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,If you gave me the chance I wouldn't stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.30,0:36:52.19,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Saying anything is incredibly fair
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.87,0:36:59.53,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Next is everybody's theories
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.53,0:37:02.00,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Tonight's presenters are
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.00,0:37:07.03,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Onigoe Tomahawk  \N-Thanks for having us
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.03,0:37:10.04,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Anti-social, anti-social people \N-No no no
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.04,0:37:17.22,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Without further ado, this time we bring you a hypothesis related to one of Yoshimoto Kogyo's senior members
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.22,0:37:18.52,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Please have a look
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.58,0:37:23.02,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,There are no young comedians who know the real name of Honkon
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.76,0:37:28.36,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Probably not
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.36,0:37:33.26,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,He was using his  real name until the end of "Gottsu ee Kanji"
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.26,0:37:36.30,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Then changed it to his stage name
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.30,0:37:38.07,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Changed to Honkon?\N -Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.07,0:37:39.47,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,How long has it been since he changed to Honkon
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.47,0:37:41.48,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,25 years
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.48,0:37:44.82,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,By the way, Iizuka, do you Honkon's real name?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.82,0:37:48.34,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Well, I watched Gottsu Ee Kanji
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.01,0:37:51.46,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,It's Kurano, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.46,0:37:54.98,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Yes, his first name is Kurano
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.98,0:37:57.30,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Matsumoto certainly knows, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.30,0:38:02.43,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,No, my memory is a little hazy
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.50,0:38:08.90,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Takahiro
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.07,0:38:11.40,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,We're not really sure
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.40,0:38:13.44,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.90,0:38:15.62,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,You're asking the question but you don't know?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.62,0:38:16.91,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.56,0:38:20.69,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Originally the group was called Hong Kong Macau
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.69,0:38:23.42,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,The group disbanded, leaving only Hong Kong
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.42,0:38:26.44,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,For some reason people started calling him Honkon Honkon
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.44,0:38:28.15,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,So that's where he got his stage name I guess
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.15,0:38:29.09,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.97,0:38:36.83,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,There are no young comedians who know the real name of Honkon
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.36,0:38:46.50,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,To verify, young comedians who debuted after Honkon's name change were tested
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.40,0:38:48.33,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,First
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.74,0:38:53.48,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Good morning
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.79,0:39:00.02,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Debuting just six years ago, The Mummy
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.18,0:39:01.45,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Please listen to the question \N-Ok
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.45,0:39:02.52,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Question?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.52,0:39:05.36,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Who is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.46,0:39:07.36,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Hello \N-Hello
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.36,0:39:09.43,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Honkon？
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.43,0:39:10.03,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Correct
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.03,0:39:11.16,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Yes \N-Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.16,0:39:13.13,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Have you ever worked with Honkon?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.43,0:39:19.94,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,We worked with him twice in Osaka
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.94,0:39:21.10,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,What impression did you have of him
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.57,0:39:26.91,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,He wears glasses backstage
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.91,0:39:31.01,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,When reading the newspaper or something, it's kind of scary
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.25,0:39:34.18,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,He's a very nice guy though
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.55,0:39:35.95,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Please listen to another question
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.51,0:39:41.73,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,What is Honkon's real name?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.56,0:39:49.13,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,This is a bit...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.13,0:39:51.37,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Honkon's real name?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.37,0:39:54.44,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,He has a pretty unique and interesting name
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.44,0:39:56.57,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,It's more of a beautiful name
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.57,0:39:57.81,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,What is it...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.81,0:40:00.24,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,It's more like a handsome man's name, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.44,0:40:03.75,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Nakayauchi Mao
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.91,0:40:05.25,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Incorrect
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.90,0:40:07.04,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Is that a handsome man?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.94,0:40:08.42,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,As expected, they don't know
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.68,0:40:10.69,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Too tough
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.36,0:40:17.19,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Next is Hanako Kikuta, who has experience in co-starring with a different agency
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.19,0:40:20.43,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,What impression do you have of him
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.43,0:40:27.70,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,He sometimes... makes political statements
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.68,0:40:26.83,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,This is what has happened recently
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.70,0:40:32.38,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,A little... a little scary
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.38,0:40:36.28,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Is that okay? He won't be mad will he?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.21,0:40:42.08,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,So, what is Honkon's real name?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.19,0:40:47.32,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Eh? Honkon's?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.49,0:40:51.83,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,What was it? I should know
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.83,0:40:53.16,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.16,0:40:55.90,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,It has "Kura" in it
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.17,0:41:00.90,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Kurama Toshikazu
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.00,0:41:04.41,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,No? Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.29,0:41:07.96,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,"Kura" was right at least
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.86,0:41:11.47,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,The next question is a junior comedian who belongs to the same agency as Honkon
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.69,0:41:19.29,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,And is also a regular on "Marco Pololi"
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.21,0:41:18.90,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Must know then
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.19,0:41:24.48,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,What is Honkon's real name?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.96,0:41:32.77,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Kurano...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.77,0:41:38.07,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Kurano Yoichi
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.17,0:41:40.08,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.21,0:41:46.58,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,But we really...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.58,0:41:52.29,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I haven't been a regular member for six months
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.29,0:41:54.76,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,We're not that close, really
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.40,0:41:54.41,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Excuse!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.41,0:41:55.51,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Is that the issue?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.51,0:41:57.42,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,The next challenger is...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.11,0:42:02.06,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Miki should know, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.30,0:42:06.87,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Not only do we often meet on shows, we also perform at the Lumine Theater once a month
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.87,0:42:09.07,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,We're often together in the green room
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.74,0:42:13.21,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Wait, what? What? So scary!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.44,0:42:15.38,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I'm scared of...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.91,0:42:19.22,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I don't really want to talk about Honkon
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.88,0:42:20.92,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,This is the most unacceptable
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.52,0:42:24.52,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Still \N -What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.19,0:42:28.19,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,He's been angry with me several times
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.42,0:42:30.59,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I did indeed do something wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.59,0:42:33.53,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Said my greeting was too shallow  \N-Too shallow?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.37,0:42:33.62,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Greeting was too shallow?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.60,0:42:35.40,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,He told me "say good morning properly!"
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.40,0:42:38.53,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,"Saying "morning" isn't good enough"
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.53,0:42:41.27,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,"Look down and say "good morning" properly!"
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.27,0:42:43.64,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,"What you're doing isn't a real greeting"
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.01,0:42:48.58,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,He got angry at the show's celebration party, where Higashino and all the staff were present
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.58,0:42:54.25,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I also had a meal with him at Lumine once
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.25,0:42:55.89,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Honkon asked, "What are you going to eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.89,0:42:56.92,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,"Soba noodles"
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.92,0:42:58.75,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,"Oh really?" "Yes."
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.75,0:43:01.36,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,"Is it good?" "Yes."
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.36,0:43:03.29,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,He scolded me, saying, "don't you wanna have a conversation!?"
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.13,0:43:07.33,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Don't want to
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.24,0:43:09.40,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Doesn't want to
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.23,0:43:13.44,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I was shouted at for not wanting to start a conversation over lunch\N  -I've been shouted at a few times for the same thing
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.44,0:43:15.61,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,"Say something!"
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.61,0:43:19.68,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,And he'd tell me "don't answer so boringly"
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.18,0:43:24.54,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,As we now know that Miki and Honkon are very close, let's get to the point
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.91,0:43:28.30,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Known
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.88,0:43:30.12,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,What is Honkon's full name
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.12,0:43:31.29,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Really?  \N-See!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.29,0:43:34.89,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Honestly, I might actually know
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.89,0:43:38.63,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,After all, you'd definitely know important senior comedians
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.63,0:43:39.63,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,You know?\N  -Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.86,0:43:43.77,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Seriously, I can't think of even a single character
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.77,0:43:45.74,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,It is similar to Honkon?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.74,0:43:48.80,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I'm not saying anything  \N-Can't think of a single character
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.97,0:43:51.71,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Forget about the validity of this theory or anything
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.71,0:43:55.28,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Not being able to answer is very rude to Honkon
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.65,0:44:02.89,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Homma... Homma Daisuke?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.50,0:44:02.36,wipe_Wed,,0,0,0,,Too much
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.89,0:44:06.66,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,That was very rude  \N-This is gonna be bad
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.76,0:44:09.69,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Can I say it?  \N-Please do
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.69,0:44:12.12,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Kurano Takahiro
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.12,0:44:12.66,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Correct
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.66,0:44:13.83,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Very good
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.33,0:44:16.23,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Very good
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.23,0:44:17.53,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Its Kurano!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.77,0:44:19.04,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Everyone is so rude
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.04,0:44:24.77,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Regarding Gottsu Ee Kanji, people always think of Downtown, Imada and Higashino
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.77,0:44:25.91,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,These main characters
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.91,0:44:27.24,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Ah wait what i'm saying is too much....
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.24,0:44:30.95,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I don't really understand what he's getting at
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.45,0:44:35.52,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,{\c&H0E00DE&\3c&HFFFFFF&}To sum up\N {\c\3c}Honkon's going to shout at everyone
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.83,0:44:39.27,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry \N -This is bad
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.27,0:44:43.53,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,If Honkon sees this he'll be angry
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.53,0:44:44.86,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,He watches all shows \N -Literally everything
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.86,0:44:47.17,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,You are the ones who brought this theory
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.17,0:44:50.13,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,We haven't met him yet
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.13,0:44:53.24,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,If possible, I hope to reach the end of my career without meeting Honkon
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.24,0:44:56.22,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,No way, you haven't met at all?  \N-No, not at all
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.22,0:44:58.86,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Really?  \N-Not at all
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.86,0:44:59.48,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Really!?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.48,0:45:04.55,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Many young comedians have warned us over the years to be careful
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.55,0:45:09.05,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,We also watched Honkon when we were young
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.05,0:45:13.24,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,But why are Downtown's henchmen still held in such high regard?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.24,0:45:14.06,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.06,0:45:15.12,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,That's scary!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.13,0:45:17.56,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,This should absolutely never be said!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.85,0:45:20.53,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Hamada, this is the guy that said it
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.53,0:45:22.47,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Even juniors wouldn't dare say such a thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.39,0:45:26.78,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, this guy is really...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.50,0:45:32.75,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,We are currently recruiting women who really like Kuro-chan
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.75,0:45:35.24,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Although the planned program is not yet confirmed
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.24,0:45:39.89,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,The specific plan will be determined according to the situation of the recruited people
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.89,0:45:41.96,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Please go to the program website to state your interest!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.05,0:46:14.75,normal_Wed,,0,0,0,,Thanks for watching. Support me and get subs early at patreon.com/zwanster03

